the automated planet finder -lrb- apf -rrb- consists of a 2.4-metre automated telescope and enclosure , and a high-resolution spectrograph . it takes starlight from the telescope and spreads it into a rainbow of colours , splitting the light into a spectrum of thousands of different wavelengths that can be measured . apf observes them every night for months , in search of rocky planets with very low masses , similar to earth .
