researchers from the university of connecticut warned animals in regions where shrinking habitats and barriers to migration compound the problem are most at risk . the extinction risk would increase from 2.8 to 5.2 per cent . if global warming maintains its current trajectory and a 4.3 degree increase , that could increase to 16 per cent , he said .
