the discovery of cremated bone , thought to be the earliest ever identified in britain , could re-write the history of mesolithic , or middle stone age burial practices . it was placed into a pit with a diameter of about three feet -lrb- one metre -rrb- and then backfilled with soil . three radiocarbon dates , two from bone fragments and one from charcoal , have confirmed the remains are around 7,614 years old .
