researchers say climate change impacted human migration . until 1.4 million years ago it was too cold to inhabit southeast spain . but then the climate warmed to 13 °c -lrb- 55 °f -rrb- and became more humid . this enabled hominins - our distant ancestors - to move to new regions . research was led by dr jordi agusti from the catalan institution for research and advanced studies .
