the maglev train completed a test run on a track in yamanashi , japan . it beat the previous record of 361mph -lrb- 580km/h -rrb- set in 2003 . maglev trains use magnets to lift the carriages above the track . this eliminates the need for wheels and therefore any incidence of friction . right now speeds are limited at up to 400 kilometres per hour .
