researchers at the university of huddersfield have created a technique which they claim can distinguish between the genetic fingerprints of identical twins . identical twins share 100 per cent of their genes , meaning that until now it has been impossible to tell which sibling a sample comes from . but as they age different life experiences , such as smoking or diet , create variations in the number of hydrogen bonds in the dna .
